Provide one example for shall and deep copy in java
Here is **one clear and simple example** showing **Shallow Copy** and **Deep Copy** in Java, explained step by step (beginner-friendly and interview-ready).

---

## Scenario

We have a `Person` object which **contains another object** `Address`.

```java
class Address {
    String city;

    Address(String city) {
        this.city = city;
    }
}

class Person {
    String name;
    Address address;

    Person(String name, Address address) {
        this.name = name;
        this.address = address;
    }
}
```

---

# 🔹 Shallow Copy Example

### Idea

* **Primitive fields** → copied
* **Object references** → shared between original and copy

### Code

```java
public class ShallowCopyExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Address address = new Address("Delhi");
        Person p1 = new Person("Amit", address);

        // Shallow copy
        Person p2 = new Person(p1.name, p1.address);

        p2.address.city = "Mumbai";

        System.out.println(p1.address.city); // Mumbai
        System.out.println(p2.address.city); // Mumbai
    }
}
```

### Output

```
Mumbai
Mumbai
```

### Explanation

* `p1` and `p2` **share the same Address object**
* Changing city via `p2` affects `p1`

👉 **This is Shallow Copy**

---

# 🔹 Deep Copy Example

### Idea

* **Both objects and nested objects are fully copied**
* No shared references

### Code

```java
public class DeepCopyExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Address address = new Address("Delhi");
        Person p1 = new Person("Amit", address);

        // Deep copy
        Address newAddress = new Address(p1.address.city);
        Person p2 = new Person(p1.name, newAddress);

        p2.address.city = "Mumbai";

        System.out.println(p1.address.city); // Delhi
        System.out.println(p2.address.city); // Mumbai
    }
}
```

### Output

```
Delhi
Mumbai
```

### Explanation

* `p2` has its **own Address object**
* Change in `p2` does **not** affect `p1`

👉 **This is Deep Copy**

---

# 🔹 Shallow vs Deep Copy (Quick Comparison)

| Feature                  | Shallow Copy | Deep Copy |
| ------------------------ | ------------ | --------- |
| Object reference         | Shared       | Separate  |
| Memory usage             | Less         | More      |
| Performance              | Faster       | Slower    |
| Side effects             | Yes          | No        |
| Safe for mutable objects | ❌            | ✅         |

---

# 🔹 Interview One-Line Answer

> **Shallow copy copies object references, while deep copy creates completely independent objects including nested objects.**

